": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMDExNzgxNzMx", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-libs", "name": "T-libs", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the library team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 7, "created_at": "2021-01-14T05:25:36Z", "updated_at": "2021-01-14T15:15:59Z", "closed_at": "2021-01-14T15:15:33Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Using the `flatten()` iterator adapter, causes broken size hints. Consider the following small example:\r\n```\r\n// Construct a simple nested iterator: 10 x 10\r\nlet t = (0..10).map(|_| (0..10));\r\n\r\n// Flatten and get its size hint\r\nprintln!(\"flat_size_hint = {:?}\", t.flatten().size_hint());\r\n```\r\nI expected to see:\r\n```\r\nflat_size_hint = (100, Some(100))\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead, I see:\r\n```\r\nflat_size_hint = (0, None)\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nMy Rust version is:\r\n```\r\n$ rustup -V\r\nrustup 1.23.1 (3df2264a9 2020-11-30)\r\ninfo: This is the version for the rustup toolchain manager, not the rustc compiler.\r\ninfo: The currently active `rustc` version is `rustc 1.48.0 (7eac88abb 2020-11-16)`\r\n```", "closed_by": {"login": "cargodog", "id": 52189564, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUyMTg5NTY0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/52189564?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog", "html_url": "https://github.com/cargodog", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cargodog/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github